    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the implementation plan:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Public Namespace\n\n### Overview\nAdd `Bun.INI.parse()` and `Bun.INI.stringify()` following the exact same pattern as `Bun.TOML`, `Bun.JSONC`, `Bun.JSON5`, and `Bun.YAML`.\n\n### 5 files to change:\n\n**1. NEW `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — Self-contained INI implementation:\n- `create()` — builds a JS object with `parse` and `stringify` JSFunctions\n- `parse()` — line-by-line parser using `std.mem.tokenizeScalar`. Skips `;`/`#` comments, handles `[section]` headers → nested JS objects, `key = value` → string properties, throws `SyntaxError` on malformed input\n- `stringify()` — iterates with `jsc.JSPropertyIterator`, does two passes: scalars first as `key = value`, then nested objects as `\\n[section]\\nk = v` blocks; uses `wtf.StringBuilder`\n- Imports at bottom (Zig convention): `std`, `bun`, `jsc`, `JSValue`, `ZigString`, `wtf`\n\n**2. `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — 4 surgical changes:\n- Import: `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;` (line ~2079)\n- Lazy prop decl: `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);` (line ~70, after YAML)\n- Export: `@export(&BunObject.INI, .{ .name = lazyPropertyCallbackName(\"INI\") });` in `exportAll()` (line ~140)\n- Getter fn: `pub fn getINIObject(...)` returning `INIObject.create(globalThis)` (after `getYAMLObject` line ~1288)\n\n**3. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Insert `macro(INI) \\` between `macro(Glob) \\` and `macro(JSON5) \\` (alphabetical, line ~12)\n\n**4. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `bunObjectTable` (after YAML at line ~968)\n\n**5. `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI` with JSDoc-documented `parse(input: string): Record<string, any>` and `stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string` (after TOML namespace at line ~794)",
